{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1770906645,"nonce":"Be/i4NNDKzg3gwxe6mjoOJssd9E=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87qYFcd","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/190","origin":"github"},"title":"Use venv-isolated pre-commit for make lint","message":"## Problem\n\n`pre-commit` is installed at the system level but its Python module is broken due to a Python version mismatch (system moved to 3.12). Installing it with `pip install` fails because of PEP 668 (`--break-system-packages` required).\n\nThis means `pre-commit run --all-files` and the existing `make lint` target (which calls shellcheck/flake8/pylint directly) don't work reliably.\n\n## Proposed Solution\n\nReplace the ad-hoc `make lint` target with one that runs `pre-commit` from a dedicated `.venv/` virtual environment. The venv:\n\n- Is created automatically on first `make lint` run\n- Keeps pre-commit and its dependencies isolated from system Python and the ROS 2 overlay\n- Never contaminates the ROS 2 environment (activated only transiently by Make's recipe)\n- Is gitignored\n\nAlso add a `make setup-dev` target for explicit bootstrapping.\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null}]}